  "text": "The copy-move attack is one type of tampering in which a region of the image is copied and pasted in another area in the same image to cover an important image feature. In [CITATION_1] a technique for detecting copy-move forgery is presented based on SURF and KD-Tree for multidimensional data matching. Shivakumar et al. designed a system to identify the duplicated areas, then extracted key points in the forged areas and matched them among the SURF features, thus determined the possibility of forgery.",
